IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO REPRESENT NON-PROFIT COMMUNITY AND FREE CLINICS THAT OPERATE PRIMARY CARE SITES IN LA.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO SERVE AND REPRESENT THE INTERESTS OF COMMUNITY CLINIC AND HEALTH CENTER MEMBERS. OUR MEMBERS PROVIDE QUALITY PRIMARY CARE (INCLUDING MEDICAL, DENTAL AND BEHAVIORAL HEALTH SERVICES) FOR THE UNINSURED AND MEDICALLY UNDERSERVED POPULATIONS.
IRS990.Desc: CCALAC (COMMUNITY CLINIC ASSOCIATION OF LOS ANGELES COUNTY) HAS GROWN TO BE THE LARGEST REGIONAL ASSOCIATION OF COMMUNITY CLINICS AND HEALTH CENTERS IN CALIFORNIA. COMMUNITY CLINICS PROVIDE PRIMARY HEALTH CARE, INCLUDING MEDICAL, DENTAL, AND MENTAL HEALTH SERVICES, TO THE UNINSURED, UNDERINSURED, WORKING POOR, HIGH-RISK AND VULNERABLE POPLULATIONS. THEY SERVE ALL, REGARDLESS OF ABILITY TO PAY. CCALAC'S CENTRAL ROLE IS TO HELP ITS MEMBERS SERVE THEIR PATIENTS IN AN EFFICIENT AND COST-EFFECTIVE MANNER WHILE THEY PROVIDE QUALITY CARE. CCALAC STRIVES TO IDENTIFY AND ADDRESS THE COLLECTIVE NEEDS OF ITS MEMBERS AT THE LOCAL, STATE AND FEDERAL LEVELS. CCALAC DELIVERS A VARIETY OF MEMBER SERVICES INCLUDING POLICY ADVOCACY, EDUCATION AND PEER SUPPORT. CCALAC CONNECTS CLINICS, SHARES AND LEVERAGES RESOURCES, INCREASES ORGANIZATIONAL CAPACITY, AND RAISES A UNIFIED VOICE ON BEHALF OF CLINICS. CCALAC ALSO PROVIDES ONGOING TRAINING AND EDUCATION FOR HEALTH CENTER STAFF.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION SENT STAFF TO ADVOCATE WITH LEGISLATORS ON HEALTH CARE ISSUES, SENT LETTERS EXPRESSING POSITIONS ON POLICY ISSUES, AUTHORED SEVERAL BLOG POSTS AND PROVIDED COMMENTS TO THE PRESS ON HEALTH CARE ISSUES, AND THE CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER MADE COMMENTS AT PUBLIC CONFERENCES AND RALLIES.

THE ORGANIZATION RECOGNIZES THE IMPACT OF TAX POSITIONS IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS IF THAT POSITION IS MORE LIKELY THAN NOT OF BEING SUSTAINED ON AUDIT, BASED ON THE TECHNICAL MERITS OF THE POSITION. TO DATE, THE ORGANIZATION HAS NOT RECORDED ANY UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS. THE ORGANIZATION RECOGNIZES POTENTIAL ACCRUED INTEREST AND PENALTIES RELATED TO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS IN INCOME TAX EXPENSE. DURING THE YEAR ENDED, THE ORGANIZATION DID NOT RECOGNIZE ANY AMOUNT IN POTENTIAL INTEREST AND PENALTIES ASSOCIATED WITH UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION HAS ONE CLASS OF MEMBERS WHO HAVE THE RIGHT TO ELECT DIRECTORS, VOTE ON THE DISPOSITION OF ALL OR SUBSTANTIALLY ALL OF THE ORGANIZATION'S ASSETS, ON ANY MERGER AND ITS PRINCIPLE TERMS AND ANY AMENDMENT TO THOSE TERMS, AND ON ANY ELECTION TO DISSOLVE THE ORGANIZATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION HAS ONE CLASS OF MEMBERS WHO HAVE THE RIGHT TO ELECT DIRECTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION HAS ONE CLASS OF MEMBERS WHO HAVE THE RIGHT TO VOTE ON THE DISPOSITION OF ALL OR SUBSTANTIALLY ALL OF THE ORGANIZATION'S ASSETS, ON ANY MERGER AND ITS PRINCIPAL TERMS AND AMENDMENT OF THOSE TERMS, AND ON ANY ELECTION TO DISSOLVE THE ORGANIZATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS REVIEWED BY JONES AND ASSOCIATES, THE CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER, AND THE CHIEF OPERATING OFFICER. A COPY OF THE FORM 990 IS THEN GIVEN TO ALL BOARD MEMBERS PRIOR TO FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: CCALAC HAS AN ANNUAL REQUIREMENT THAT OFFICERS, DIRECTORS OR TRUSTEES AND KEY EMPLOYEES FILL OUT A CONFLICT OF INTEREST QUESTIONNAIRE. THE CEO MONITORS THE COMPLIANCE OF THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY BY REVIEWING THE ANNUAL QUESTIONNAIRES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE PERSONNEL COMMITTEE REVIEWS AND APPROVES THE CEO'S COMPENSATION BY COMPARING COMPENSATION FOR SIMILARLY QUALIFIED PERSONS IN FUNCTIONALLY COMPARABLE POSITIONS AT SIMILARLY SITUATED ORGANIZATIONS. THE COMPENSATION DETERMINATION IS THEN PRESENTED TO THE BOARD FOR APPROVAL INDEPENDENTLY, WITHOUT THE PARTICIPATION OF INTERESTED PARTIES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
PROFESSIONAL SERVICES AND SUBCONTRACTORS: PROGRAM SERVICE EXPENSES 974,234. MANAGEMENT AND GENERAL EXPENSES 48,553. FUNDRAISING EXPENSES 35,000. TOTAL EXPENSES 1,057,787.
